						<div class="postbody">If you haven't seen it already, I strongly recommend this excellent article from the wiki on how to handle NMI, what to put where, and best methods for VRAM writes during vblank. It's probably the single best resource for NES-specific &quot;best practice&quot;.<br /><br />That said, a ton of commercial games don't follow these guidelines. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_frame_and_NMIs">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_frame_and_NMIs</a><!-- m --></div>

