					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Fri May 08, 2015 7:17 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 2200<br /><b>Location:</b> DIGDUG
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I believe the &quot;split&quot; method is the best.<br /><br />The NMI code should push VRAM updates (if they are ready), push the sprites to OAM, set the scroll, update the music. These things NEED to be done every frame, during v-blank (except music).<br /><br />The main code can handle the rest.<br /><br />I think Shiru's neslib has a good example of an NMI code.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
