						<div class="postbody">If I recall correctly, NESASM has weird quirks about indentation. Like, some of the directives would break if you tabbed them in, or didn't tab it in. I can't remember.<br /><br />Maybe some small oddity of syntax is throwing you off.<br /><br />Quote from Kasumi...<br />&quot;nesasm gives <span style="color: #80FF80">unknown instruction</span> when you don't indent with whitespace characters.&quot;<br /><br />From...<br /><!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=7922">viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=7922</a><!-- l --><br /><br />Edit: personal opinion. Drop NESASM now and start using asm6 or ca65.</div>

					
