					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Absolutely. <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Controller_Reading" class="postlink">You can easily store all 8 button states on a single NES controller in a single byte</a>, with each bit indicating wether the button is pressed. I also do comparisons with the previous NMI to see if a button was just pressed to trigger events on button pulses (such as attacking or jumping), and store those in a separate byte.</div>

